Business Domain: Insurance
Define the business problem:
what problem is being solved ? - claim fraud detection
who are the users or stakeholders ?-
Insurance Companies	Use the AI system to detect fraudulent claims
Claim Investigators	Review suspicious claims flagged by the model
Insurance Agents	Handle customer claims and policy information
Customers / Policyholders	Submit insurance claims
Fraud Detection Teams	Monitor and investigate fraud patterns
Data Scientists / AI Engineers	Build and maintain the fraud detection model
Compliance & Regulatory Teams	Ensure fair and legal claim processing
Business Managers	Monitor operational efficiency and fraud reduction
What is the current manual or traditional process ?
The traditional/manual process for insurance claim fraud detection mainly relies on human review, rule-based checks, 
and investigation teams to identify suspicious claims.
What are the limitations of the current process ?
It is usually slower, labor-intensive, and less scalable compared to AI-based systems.
AI task type: Anomaly detection / Classification
Anomaly detection and classification are suitable AI task types for insurance claim fraud detection because fraudulent claims 
usually behave differently from normal claims and can therefore be identified as unusual patterns or classified into 
fraud/non-fraud categories.
